            <c02 level="class">
               <did>
                  <unitid type="work">poems.bapo</unitid>
                  <unittitle type="uniform" label="Uniform Title:">
                     <title render="doublequote" linktype="simple">The Bard. A Pindaric Ode</title>
                  </unittitle>
                  <unittitle label="First Line:">
                     <title linktype="simple">'Ruin seize thee, ruthless king!</title>
                  </unittitle>
                  <unitdate normal="1757" era="ce" calendar="gregorian">1757</unitdate>
               </did>
               <bibliography>
                  <bibref title="http://www.thomasgray.org/resources/biblp.shtml#S/H_1966"
                          linktype="simple">Starr/Hendrickson (eds.), <title render="italic" linktype="simple">Complete Poems</title> (1966),  18-24</bibref>
                  <bibref title="http://www.thomasgray.org/resources/biblp.shtml#LoR_1969"
                          linktype="simple">Lonsdale (ed.), <title render="italic" linktype="simple">Poems</title> (1969),  177-200</bibref>
               </bibliography>
               <scopecontent>
                  <p>Begun late in <extref href="http://www.thomasgray.org/resources/table.shtml#1754"
                             show="replace"
                             linktype="simple">
                        <date normal="1754" era="ce" calendar="gregorian">1754</date>
                     </extref> and initially abandoned by 
							<date normal="175508" era="ce" calendar="gregorian">August 1755</date>, then taken up again, completed
							and revised, between <extref href="http://www.thomasgray.org/resources/table.shtml#1757"
                             show="replace"
                             linktype="simple">
                        <date normal="175705/175708" era="ce" calendar="gregorian">May and August 
								1757</date>
                     </extref>. <persname normal="Gray, Thomas, 1716-1771" source="lcnaf">Gray</persname> sent	the earlier parts of the poem in
							letters to <extref href="http://www.thomasgray.org/resources/glnames.shtml#Wharton, Thomas,          1717-1794"
                             show="replace"
                             linktype="simple">
                        <persname role="trc" normal="Wharton, Thomas,           1717-1794">Thomas Wharton</persname>
                     </extref>, dated <extref href="http://www.thomasgray.org/cgi-bin/display.cgi?text=tgal0230"
                             show="replace"
                             linktype="simple">
                        <date normal="17550806" era="ce" calendar="gregorian">6 August
											1755</date>
                     </extref> (ll. 1-56), and to <extref href="http://www.thomasgray.org/resources/glnames.shtml#Stonhewer, Richard, 1728-1809"
                             show="replace"
                             linktype="simple">
                        <persname role="trc" normal="Stonhewer, Richard,              1728-1809">Richard Stonhewer</persname>
                     </extref>, dated 
							<extref href="http://www.thomasgray.org/cgi-bin/display.cgi?text=tgal0235"
                             show="replace"
                             linktype="simple">
                        <date normal="17550821" era="ce" calendar="gregorian">21 
								August 1755</date>
                     </extref> (ll. 63-100), the latter part (ll. 111-144) to 
							<extref href="http://www.thomasgray.org/resources/glnames.shtml#Mason, William, 1724-1797"
                             show="replace"
                             linktype="simple">
                        <persname normal="Mason, William, 1724-1797">William
										Mason</persname>
                     </extref>, dated <extref href="http://www.thomasgray.org/cgi-bin/display.cgi?text=tgal0271"
                             show="replace"
                             linktype="simple">
                        <date normal="17570524/17570531" era="ce" calendar="gregorian">[24 
											or 31] May 1757</date>
                     </extref>.
							First published, as <title render="doublequote" linktype="simple">Ode II.</title>
							in <title render="italic" linktype="simple">Odes by Mr. Gray</title> (<date normal="1757" type="publication" era="ce" calendar="gregorian">1757</date>), <extref href="http://www.thomasgray.org/cgi-bin/view.cgi?collection=primary&amp;edition=1757&amp;text=bapo"
                             show="replace"
                             linktype="simple">12-21</extref>.</p>
               </scopecontent>
